{"title_page": "Little Falls station", "text_new": "{{For|the historic railway station in Little Falls, Minnesota|Northern Pacific Railway Depot (Little Falls, Minnesota)}}\n{{Coord|40|52|50|N|74|14|07|W|display=title|type:railwaystation}}\n{{Infobox Station\n | name=Little Falls\n | style=NJ Transit\n | image=Little_Falls_Station_-_September_2014.jpg\n | image_caption=Little Falls station building in September&nbsp;2014 facing eastbound towards Great Notch.\n | address=Union Avenue, [[Little Falls, New Jersey|Little Falls, NJ]] 07424\n | coordinates=\n | line=\n | other={{bus icon|12px|NJT Bus}} '''[[New Jersey Transit Bus Operations|NJT Bus]]''': [[List of New Jersey Transit bus routes (1-99)|11]], [[List of NJ Transit bus routes (100-199)|191]], [[List of NJ Transit bus routes (700-799)|704, and 705]]<br>(on Main Street)\n | platform=1 [[side platform]]\n | levels=\n | tracks=1 revenue track and 1 siding \n | parking=194 parking spaces\n | bicycle=Lockers available\n | passengers=165 (average weekday)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.nj.com/bergen_impact/other/1Q2013.pdf |title=QUARTERLY RIDERSHIP TRENDS ANALYSIS |publisher=New Jersey Transit |accessdate=January 4, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6DEGzJnox?url=http://media.nj.com/bergen_impact/other/1Q2013.pdf |archivedate=December 27, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://patch.com/new-jersey/hoboken/how-many-riders-use-nj-transit-s-hoboken-train-station|title=How Many Riders Use NJ Transit's Hoboken Train Station?|work=Hoboken Patch|access-date=2018-07-18|language=en}}</ref>\n | pass_year=2017\n | pass_percent=\n | pass_system=\n | rebuilt=1915<ref name=\"yanosey\">{{cite book|last=Yanosey|first=Robert J.|title=Erie Railroad Facilities (In Color)|publisher=Morning Sun Books Inc.|location=[[Scotch Plains, New Jersey]]|year=2006|volume=Volume 1: New Jersey|pages=76|isbn=1-58248-183-0}}</ref>\n | closed=\n | opened=January 1, 1873{{sfn|Catlin|1873|p=33}}{{sfn|Whittemore|1894|p=47}}{{sfn|Baxter|1999|p=147}} \n | electrified=Not electrified\n | ADA=\n | code=1765 (Erie Railroad)<ref name=\"codes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jon-n-bevliles.net/RAILROAD/erie_docs/erie-losn16.html|title=List of Station Names and Numbers|date=May 1, 1916|publisher=[[Erie Railroad]]|location=[[Jersey City, New Jersey]]|accessdate=November 23, 2010}}</ref>\n | owned=[[NJ Transit]]\n | zone=8\n | former=\n | services= {{Adjacent stations|system1=NJ Transit\n|line1=Montclair-Boonton|left1=Wayne Route 23|right1=Montclair State University\n|line2=Montclair-Boonton|left2=Wayne Route 23|right2=Great Notch|note-right2=(closed 2010)\n}}\n | other_services_header = Former services\n | other_services_collapsible = yes\n | other_services = {{Adjacent stations|system1=Erie Railroad\n|line1=New York and Greenwood Lake Railway|left1=Mountain View|right1=Great Notch\n|line2=New York and Greenwood Lake Railway|left2=Singac|right2=Great Notch|note-left2=(closed)\n}}\n | mpassengers=\n}}\n'''Little Falls''' is the second of two stations maintained by [[NJ Transit]] in [[Little Falls, New Jersey]]. The station, on the [[Montclair-Boonton Line]] is the first to receive limited revenue service due to the end of electrification at the site of the former [[Great Notch (NJT station)|Great Notch station]]. Little Falls station, located at Union Avenue ([[List of county routes in Passaic County, New Jersey#646|Passaic County Route 646]]) in downtown has one side platform with the 1915 station depot, built of brick on the side. The station contains one track for revenue service, and a passing siding for trains. The station is the eighth fare zone, costing $8 for a one-way ticket to [[Hoboken Terminal]] and  $1.25 more to transfer at [[Newark Broad Street]] to [[New York Pennsylvania Station]]. The station has 194 parking spaces, 134 on Railroad Avenue at Montclair Avenue and 60 more along Montclair Avenue. A ticket machine is available. The station is not accessible for handicapped persons. Anyone wishing to receive train service for handicapped must go to [[Montclair State University (NJT station)|Montclair State University station]] or [[Wayne-Route 23 (NJT station)|Wayne Route 23 Transit Center]] across the [[Passaic River]] in [[Wayne, New Jersey|Wayne]].\n\n== Station layout and services ==\nTrains on the northbound service this station after [[Montclair State University (NJT station)|Montclair State University Station]] on Clove Road.<ref name=\"NJT-04-023\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.njtransit.com/tm/tm_servlet.srv?hdnPageAction=PressReleaseTo&PRESS_RELEASE_ID=1526|title=Montclair State University Station and  1,500-Spot Parking Deck Officially Opens: \"See More Spots\" marketing campaign begins|date=October 20, 2004|publisher=[[New Jersey Transit]]|accessdate=October 10, 2009}}</ref> As of the November 7, 2010, five inbound (to Hoboken) trains stop at Little Falls on weekday mornings, while ten outbound trains (from Hoboken) stop on weekday afternoons/evenings (The last train requires a transfer at Montclair State University Station.) There is no weekend service to Little Falls, as all service terminates at [[Bay Street (NJT station)|Bay Street station]] in [[Montclair, New Jersey]]. However, during holidays, three of extra trains heading to [[Lake Hopatcong (NJT station)|Lake Hopatcong]] stop at Little Falls along with three heading to [[Hoboken Terminal]]. Bus service is provided by New Jersey Transit with four lines meeting at Little Falls station by the No. 11, No. 191, No. 704 and No. 705.\n\n{|cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray; border-bottom:solid 1px gray\" rowspan=4 width=75|'''Ground/<br>Platform level'''\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;\"|Street level\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;\"|Station building, ticket machine and parking\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 2px black;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Side platform]], doors will open on the left or right</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100|'''Outbound/Inbound'''\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=650|\u2190 {{rcb|system=NJ Transit|line=Montclair-Boonton|inline=yes}} PM rush hours toward [[Hackettstown station|Hackettstown]] <small>([[Wayne Route 23 Transit Center|Wayne Route 23]])</small><br>{{0|\u2190}} {{rcb|system=NJ Transit|line=Montclair-Boonton|inline=yes}} AM rush hours toward [[Hoboken Terminal|Hoboken]] or [[Pennsylvania Station (New York City)|New York]] <small>([[Montclair State University station|Montclair State University]])</small> \u2192\n|}\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Little Falls Station September 2013.jpg|left|thumb|The 1915-construction station depot at Little Falls, seen in September&nbsp;2013]]\nThe station is located along the [[Montclair-Boonton Line]], a former alignment of the [[New York and Greenwood Lake Railway (1878\u20131943)|New York and Greenwood Lake Railway]], run by the Erie Railroad. The line ran from the Erie's [[Pavonia Terminal]] in Jersey City to [[Sterling Forest (Erie Railroad station)|Sterling Forest station]] on the [[New Jersey]] / [[New York (state)|New York]] state line. The station was the second of three built in Little Falls, with Great Notch station in the Great Notch district and the [[Singac (Erie Railroad station)|Singac]] station.<ref name=\"1920map\">{{cite map|title=Map of Erie Railroad Stations|year=1920|publisher=[[Erie Railroad]]|cartography=Erie Railroad}}</ref> The current railroad depot was built by the Erie in 1915, a one-story brick structure. The line was cut back to [[Wanaque-Midvale (Erie Railroad station)|Wanaque-Midvale station]] in 1935 and the cut entirely in 1966 after being rechristened as the Boonton Line, a mix of the New York and Greenwood Lake and the [[Delaware, Lackawanna and Western Railroad]]'s [[Boonton Branch]]. In 1983, seven years after the death of the [[Erie-Lackawanna Railroad]], New Jersey Transit took over railroad operations and maintenance of the building. Formerly the third station in Little Falls, it has become the only one in downtown Little Falls, after Great Notch was closed by New Jersey Transit in January 2010.<ref name=\"closing\">{{cite web|url=http://www.njtransit.com/tm/tm_servlet.srv?hdnPageAction=PressReleaseTo&PRESS_RELEASE_ID=2574|title=New Jersey Transit Announces Closure of Great Notch Station|date=December 21, 2009|publisher=New Jersey Transit|accessdate=21 December 2009|location=Newark, New Jersey}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Singac, New Jersey]]\n\n== Bibliography ==\n\n*{{cite book |last2=Adams|first2=Arthur G.|last1=Baxter |first1=Raymond J. |title=Railroad Ferries of the Hudson: And Stories of a Deckhand |date=1999 |publisher=[[Fordham University Press]] |location=[[Fordham, New York]] |isbn=9780823219544|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Catlin |first1=George L. |title=Homes on the Montclair Railway, for New York Business Men. A Description of the Country Adjacent to the Montclair Railway, Between Jersey City and Greenwood Lake |url=https://archive.org/details/homesonmontclair00catl |date=1873 |publisher=Montclair Railway Company |location=[[New York, New York]]|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Whittemore |first1=Henry |title=History of Montclair Township, State of New Jersey: Including the History of Families who Have Been Identified with Its Growth and Prosperity |date=1894 |publisher=The Suburban Publishing Company |location=New York, New York |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofmontcla00whit_0 |accessdate=February 6, 2020|ref=harv}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Little Falls (NJT station)}}\n{{NJT links}}\n* [https://maps.google.com/?ie=UTF8&ll=40.881408,-74.236096&spn=0.003837,0.013679&z=17&layer=c&cbll=40.881408,-74.236096&panoid=1OFD1wA_URjmmgrowfMwSg&cbp=12,127.8,,0,1.05 Station from Montclair Avenue from Google Maps Street View]\n\n{{NJT stations navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSO